    "approved_for_compilation": true,
    "summary": "A4 preserves the fixed SOTA target while rejecting the failed S9H production candidate as completion evidence. It routes execution into S9I frontier review and at most one S9J candidate under unchanged focused and canonical gates.",
    "counterexamples_considered": [
      "S9H trace locality elimination cannot satisfy O-causal-performance-evidence because the focused matrix regressed HTTPS proxy throughput and latency.",
      "A4 cannot be used to weaken SOTA thresholds because semantic_base, required outcomes, required result paths, and numeric hard-threshold policy are preserved.",
      "S9I is non-terminal review only; it cannot produce SOTA completion or final counterexample evidence.",
      "S9J may satisfy O-causal-performance-evidence only with fresh real-client-path, fair same-process libcurl, unchanged focused pass bar, and unchanged canonical SOTA matrix evidence."
    ],
    "required_fixes": [],
    "conditions": [
      "S9I must identify a non-duplicative causal surface with measured headroom or reject continuation rather than authorize S9J.",
      "S9J must not cite S9H locality elimination, focused matrix, or rejected runtime candidate as completion evidence.",
      "S10 and goal_achieved remain forbidden until S9J passes and a runtime Counterexample Gate covers all required steps, outcomes, and result paths."
